OL,6,F"It's a very challenging environment
OL,7,Fto work in. The support of my
OL,8,Fcolleagues was invaluable to my
OL,9,Frecovery. We're like one big family.
OL,10,FIt was not nice for them to witness
OL,11,Fwhat had happened and have to carry
OL,12,Fon. I can't thank everyone who helped
OL,13,Fme enough." said Mr YoungJPhillips, of
OL,14,FGatcombe Road in Hartcliffe, Bristol,
OL,15,Fadmitted grievous bodily harm (GBH)
OL,16,Fover the prison wounding. Moshen, of
OL,17,FAlexandra Road in Newport, admitted
OL,18,Factual bodily harm (ABH).JMoshen's
OL,19,Fbarrister Joshua Scouller said Moshen
OL,20,Fhad issues with maturity, cognitive
OL,21,Fability and impulsiveness. "He was
OL,22,Fcloser in mental age to someone who
OL,23,Fwould have been 15, if not younger, at
OL,24,Fthe time of the (prison) offence.
