OL,6,FHe added: "His involvement was rather
OL,7,Fmore fleeting than Mr Phillips'."
OL,8,FPhillips' barrister Ian Morrell said:
OL,9,F"Initially he believed he was
OL,10,Fsuffering an attack and acted in self-
OL,11,Fdefence against Mr Young.
OL,13,F"That, in large measure, perhaps
OL,14,Fexplains why there was a delay in him
OL,15,Fpleading guilty to the offence. Mr
OL,16,FPhillips has apologised to Mr Young,
OL,17,Fwith whom he had and still has an
OL,18,Faffable relationship."JThe judge,
OL,19,FRecorder David Elias KC, noted that Mr
OL,20,FYoung had been stamped on "very hard".
